  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be able to edit transaction amount in the wallet by deleting certain number of symbols\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: All symbols after dot/comma erased if editing decimal number in the amount field when sending/requesting transaction from wallet \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nOnly the last symbol is deleted \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAll symbols after the dot are deleted, only `0` left in the amount field \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Navigate to Wallet\r\n- Click Send transaction button\r\n- Type `0.0005` into the Amount field\r\n- Tap Delete (backspace) button on the keyboard once\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly build from April 27\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n",
